  "texts": [
    "5A collective of actors and entities all made important contributions to an output.",
    "Credit for this output should be distributed between these contributors according to the nature and significance of the contributions made.",
    "CCC, of course, is not the first view to emphasize that artistic, literary and other forms of production often take the format of co-creation.",
    "But contra existing views, CCC does not aim at offering neat, principled categorizations between different subgroups of agents, e.g.",
    "authors, creators, contributors, assistants [4,6,7,9,29,38,54,56]."
